    "extras": [
      "Dry season from November to April is the sweet spot; February and March usually have the clearest mornings for Antigua viewpoints, Atitlán sunrises, and Tikal wildlife walks.",
      "Keep small bills for chicken buses, public lanchas on Lake Atitlán, church donations, and Lanquín jeep rides because card acceptance drops fast outside the capital and Antigua.",
      "Book TAG flights and high-season Antigua stays early, especially around Christmas, New Year, and Semana Santa.",
      "If you skip the Flores flight, Litegua and Pullmantur overnight buses save a hotel night, but bring a light layer because the air-conditioning can feel cold.",
      "Chichicastenango is most rewarding on Thursday and Sunday market days; on other days you may prefer adding that time to Antigua or Lake Atitlán instead."
    ],
